eb Client 5.0.1 depends on Vert.x Core with Netty 4.2.2.Final; the existing 5.0.0 scaffold already documents required Java 25 native-run Netty unsafe-access system properties, but applies them only to 5.0.0.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"For native test execution of io.vertx:vertx-web-client:5.0.1 on JDK 25, set runtime system properties `-Dsun.misc.unsafe.memory.access=allow` and `-Dio.netty.tryReflectionSetAccessible=true`; do not keep the existing workaround limited only to libraryVersion == '5.0.0'. Meaningful coverage can use an in-process Vert.x HttpServer on 127.0.0.1 plus temp files for form/multipart/stream cases; no external service is required.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The optional `io.vertx:vertx-auth-oauth2` dependency is only needed for OAuth2-specific session coverage, not for ordinary WebClient request/response, caching, cookies, redirects, forms, multipart, or streaming coverage.\",\n    \"Local Gradle and Native Image verification remain authoritative; if the native run still fails after the Netty system properties, the remaining issue is likely metadata/runtime behavior rather than missing test setup.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_020dbaa000c49ece016a3eb3b33c448194b0779b77e6ec66c6\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1048, "output": 762, "cacheRead": 34816, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 36626, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782494123768, "responseId": "resp_020dbaa000c49ece016a3eb3ac56648194a2653b0f07ddfdf2"}}
